After joining BMD, I got a chance to test myself in a completely different situation. It is a completely different environment, 
a small company of 30-35 developers who are dedicatedly working on product development and delivering without fail in a fast paced environment.
Being small organisation, they have continued their startup culture and call themself startup. 
Every employee be it a Product Manager, Director, SSE or SE takes their responsibility and contribute to company's growth.
On the other hand BMD does not follow any process of SDLC, they only use jira and fisheye for tracking the development. 
For a new joinee it is little chanllenging because there is no knowlegde transfer, no documents to build understand understanding and code flow.
All one can do is to browse the code to get the understanding of the product and coding standard(followed strictly in BMD).

On the second day I got an assignment to work on Image explorer with minimal image handling functionality, deadline was 2 weeks.
I had to complete it in a week as there are going to be more number of iterations for code review or new requirements may follow. 
I completed in 4 days but as expected a new requirement followed which took 1 additional day to complete.  There was 

software development or knowledge sharing for 
Taking the decision to join BMD was like challenging myselfFor me it was a challenge to

Challenges: 
1. Spec 26-30 fps, but need to support 60, 120 fps camera
2. HW limitation, need dual decoder but have only one.
3. Performance optimization - Introduced Cache 200%(50% before timeline and 50% after)
			      Display/Playback video at player resolution instead resizing of video resolution.
			      

